g.title: COMMENT_9f82320+1
g.text: Advance the time to start the CORRECTOR step

g.title: COMMENT_9f834a0+1
g.text: Zero out energy and mass balance arrays

g.title: COMMENT_9dfac80+1
g.text: Check for creation or removal of obsructions

g.title: COMMENT_9dfb620+1
g.text: Finite differences for mass and momentum equations for the second half of the time step

g.title: COMMENT_9f8e8a0+1
g.text: Exchange species mass fractions.

g.title: COMMENT_9f8e920+1
g.text: Apply mass and species boundary conditions, update radiation, particles, and re-compute divergence

g.title: COMMENT_9f9ba40+1
g.text: Perform droplet mass/energy transfer, then move all particles, then transfer momentum to the gas.
Solid particle mass/energy transfer is handled by WALL_BC.

g.title: COMMENT_9f93cc0+1
g.text: Exchange the number of particles sent from mesh to mesh (7), and if non-zero, exchange particles (11)

g.title: COMMENT_9f93fa0+1
g.text: Update the temperature, species and gas density boundary conditions at all surfaces

g.title: COMMENT_9fa5060+1
g.text: Radiation

g.title: COMMENT_9fa8860+1
g.text: Only do an MPI exchange of radiation intensity if multiple iterations are requested.

g.title: COMMENT_9faa7e0+1
g.text: Start the computation of the divergence term.

g.title: COMMENT_9faaca0+1
g.text: In most LES fire cases, a correction to the source term in the radiative transport equation is needed.

g.title: COMMENT_9fac560+1
g.text: Exchange global pressure zone information

g.title: COMMENT_9faa440+1
g.text: Update global pressure matrices after zone connections

g.title: COMMENT_9fae580+1
g.text: Exchange mass loss information for OBSTs abutting interpolated boundaries

g.title: COMMENT_9faf6e0+1
g.text: Finish computing the divergence

g.title: COMMENT_9fb1ba0+1
g.text: Solve the pressure equation.

g.title: COMMENT_9f9fbc0+1
g.text: Update the velocity.

g.title: COMMENT_9fb4e00+1
g.text: Compute linked velocity arrays. Flux average final velocity to cutfaces.

g.title: COMMENT_9fa7320+1
g.text: Exchange velocity, pressure, particles at interpolated boundaries

g.title: COMMENT_9faf800+1
g.text: Exchange radiation intensity at interpolated boundaries if only one iteration of the solver is requested.

g.title: COMMENT_9fb7d40+1
g.text: Force normal components of velocity to match at interpolated boundaries

g.title: COMMENT_9fb82e0+1
g.text: Apply velocity boundary conditions, and update values of HRR, DEVC, etc.

g.title: COMMENT_9fbaa60+1
g.text: Share device, HRR, mass data among all processes
